        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "2. Mitigation Playbook"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Ops role maintains a runbook for each class of production incident. A runbook is a pre-written, step-by-step guide that any on-call engineer can execute under pressure without needing deep knowledge of the underlying systems. The most important mitigation actions for LLMOps incidents are listed below."
          }
        ]
