        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Ops role in LLMOps is the operational layer that keeps a production LLM system healthy: triaging incidents, executing mitigation playbooks, tuning guardrails, monitoring the eval pipeline, managing provider relationships, and running a postmortem culture that turns every incident into a system improvement. The Ops role's unique LLMOps challenges \u2014 judge literacy, prompt context requirements, guardrail calibration \u2014 distinguish it from traditional software operations and require practitioners who understand both the infrastructure and the quality properties of LLM outputs."
